Marrakech,YRzBoL2qhp8,UgzNwOoH278JFIYvQzF4AaABAg.AT-bu_n-uu0AT4jocKISAZ,UgzNwOoH278JFIYvQzF4AaABAg,@ReigneOrShine,"Thanks a lot to you for watching and for appreciating our video! Unfortunately, in Morocco we were advised at every moment to buy bottled water to drink. For brushing the teeth should be OK, as long as you don't use much and do not swallow it. We have been using travel probiotics before and during our last trips to minimise the risk of getting sick while travelling to countries where stomach issues are more common. Have a wonderful trip to Marrakech! 🇲🇦❤️😊",2026-02-11T09:43:35Z,2026-02-11T09:43:35Z,0,True,,2026-05-04T02:01:36.717363
Marrakech,YRzBoL2qhp8,Ugx80bbJ7M5JrA0E-3x4AaABAg.ASv3g80a8txASvQBONCRFb,Ugx80bbJ7M5JrA0E-3x4AaABAg,@ReigneOrShine,Thank you so much for watching our video! We're glad you enjoyed it. 😊🇲🇦❤️,2026-02-07T09:30:55Z,2026-02-07T09:30:55Z,0,True,,2026-05-04T02:01:36.817914
Marrakech,YRzBoL2qhp8,UgxTp6b5WYuFEVJksb14AaABAg.ASZP12Av_EiASZgKJPrWKX,UgxTp6b5WYuFEVJksb14AaABAg,@ReigneOrShine,"I said in the video that I was overwhelmed with the noise, crowd and fellow tourists. I have a love-hate relationship with the market. And you have no right to say that we are dishonest in our video. We go out as early as possible to beat the crowd,  and heat and it is always quieter in the morning. It is your fault for going out late then complain if it’s crowded. You should know the culture of the places that you visit. We also gave tips in the video, which you would know, IF you watched and listened to be careful of scammers. We knew about that by watching other travel videos and reading blogs before going. Again, it was your fault for not preparing yourself mentally of all the possibilities. Tourists are there to learn their culture, not to change it. If you did not like your experience, you have no right to accuse us of being dishonest when we clearly mentioned everything. Next time, before you talk, you listen to everything we say and have better understanding. If you do not like the crowd, go in the mountains!",2026-01-29T13:38:09Z,2026-01-29T14:09:37Z,0,True,,2026-05-04T02:01:36.962712
Marrakech,YRzBoL2qhp8,Ugzs9puqC2ntGK4HaJl4AaABAg.AS9upg_t3KdAScDA7YCgl5,Ugzs9puqC2ntGK4HaJl4AaABAg,@ReigneOrShine,"It's Chano here answering your comment, I am from Spain and I grew up in a Christian family, in case you may think I am Muslim because I love travelling to Morocco and learning about their history and culture. 
There is not historic evidence about a church being located where the Koutoubia Mosque was built. But our Cathedral of Sevilla was built on top of a previous mosque, and the old minaret was transformed into the beautiful Giralda bell tower, which is considered the architectural sister of the Koutoubia Minaret. 
The Spanish Christians built many churches on top of mosques after the Reconquista of Al-Andalus, and the Arabs did the same before as well, building mosques on top of Roman temples and Visigothic churches. And the Romans did the same on top of other religions temples. It was very common to repurpose materials or sites from previous religious buildings.
If you try to spread misinformation in our content we will have to block you. We respect different religions and ideas, so please do not spam our comment section with hatred. Thanks.",2026-01-30T22:31:35Z,2026-01-30T22:31:35Z,0,True,,2026-05-04T02:01:37.046758
