Tourism,9qdTCYPrAN0,Ugy4_VFG-jqI9aoDBcF4AaABAg,,@rantu9674,"So I am responding here because it is your latest post. I have worked with airports for years, mostly in the US ... I am Canadian and back, thank goodness.  Privatising an airport is not to give it exclusively to one private company that can dictate terms.  It is a matter of setting up Airport Authorities that are not-for-profit, which make the best decisions on behalf of the airport and its users.  The benefit is that in this case, Canada can use the amount of money gained to reduce debt, build infrastructure, etc.  The government still has a say through grants and loans.  This is common around the world.",2026-05-03T22:45:13Z,2026-05-03T22:45:13Z,0,False,0.0,2026-05-04T02:02:15.797212
