Tourism,tcGjKt8XRTI,UgyQdbrhObdkrsIceQB4AaABAg,,@alanwolfe9390,"We just got back from two weeks in Paris.  We rented an apartment in the 5th, not far from Rue Mouffetard, and managed to avoid the worst of the tourists. The students, at least in the evening, were worse.  We also avoided the usual attractions, Eiffel Tower, Louvre, Orsay and so on.  We did visit the Galleries Lafayette, which was fun but crowded with tourists. We're lucky, we enjoy just being in Paris, wandering through the parks, Jardin des Plants, Monceau and so on. I hate to think what it might be like in June or July, and even May would probably be a challenge.  All that said, we had two weeks with no rain an lots of sun, discovered a new and very tasty cheese (Brie de Melon), strongly flavored and not for every one, and unfortunately not available in the US.",2026-05-03T21:45:25Z,2026-05-03T21:45:25Z,1,False,0.0,2026-05-04T02:02:17.477919
