Tourism,tcGjKt8XRTI,UgyGTBdgjv3gjnD0vRd4AaABAg,,@fldon2306,"Live in Central Florida, near The Mouse and The Universe, and all that traffic, but, no State Income Taxes... So, have to take the ""bad"" with the ""good""... Taxes, such as Hotel Bed Taxes, Cruise/Port Taxes, and Immigration (Visitors) Taxes can curtail volumes of visitors. With the Theme Parks, pricing can deter visitors. Disney has taken flack for its higher prices. And, in many instances, a government can Outright Control the number of visitors, such as when I visited both the Galapagos and Machu Picchu; limiting the number of visitors and charging admission to sustain these sites.",2026-05-03T20:44:03Z,2026-05-03T20:44:03Z,0,False,0.0,2026-05-04T02:02:17.478034
