Tourism,tcGjKt8XRTI,UgziOCIokQBClJfdftF4AaABAg,,@LynnMarlowe,"As someone who lived in Hawaii for over 20 years, I understand all too well the impact of over-tourism. Even though tourism is Hawaii’s driving economy, years of ill-behaving tourists trampling the islands have had its negative effects. The problem with “Instagram-able” locations being over-run by humans comes down to one thing: greed. Only those who can afford to travel the world are the ones ruining it for the locals. The tourist that thinks because they have money to spend they have the right to visit and stay in these tourist destinations without respecting the local community. They see their friend’s posts online and decide they must go see it in person as well. It’s almost like it’s their God-given right to travel there. But just because you can, doesn’t mean you should.",2026-05-03T18:20:34Z,2026-05-03T18:20:34Z,1,False,0.0,2026-05-04T02:02:17.478260
