AFCON,MU-oq7Nthp8,UgwP6MvFihHLiz3i1at4AaABAg,,@averagemoroccanguy,"On November 12th 2016, Senegal was facing South Africa in the World Cup 2018 Qualifiers. The game was 1-1 and the referee awarded South Africa a non-existent penalty which gave them a 2-1 victory. Senegal protested to FIFA. FIFA investigated and found the referee guilty for intentionally making false decisions to ""make certain bets successful"", and they eventually banned him for life on March 2017, roughly 4 months after the match ended. The match was replayed on November 10th 2017, yes, an entire YEAR later, and ended 2-0 for Senegal, so they qualified to the World Cup.

      If y'all have no problem with a decision coming out a year after the match, then you should have no problem with a decision coming out 2 months later, otherwise you're just shameless hypocrites.",2026-03-23T14:32:37Z,2026-03-23T14:32:37Z,0,False,0.0,2026-05-04T02:02:49.716208
