Nobody outside of Moroccans takes this decision seriously, we all saw that Senegal beat Morocco in the final, overcoming blatant cheating and Senegal are the real champions",2026-03-29T23:04:49Z,2026-03-29T23:04:49Z,0,True,,2026-05-04T02:02:50.015796
AFCON,MU-oq7Nthp8,Ugy9nZDnBD4qSo4pb4F4AaABAg.AUvMhAHohJCAUxezcXsLq3,Ugy9nZDnBD4qSo4pb4F4AaABAg,@DMM6,"@anthonysmurthwaite6258 You clearly are biased against morocco because you're talking absolute nonsense. How was Morocco cheating all game? Also, there is something called an APPEALS PROCESS, which is a legal recourse that every nation member of CAF are entitled to use in situations like this. You shouldn't be upset that Morocco exercised their legal right. You should be upset that Senegal left the pitch in the first place. According to the letter of the law, that's an automatic forfeit. 

As for your silly claim that nobody outside of Morocco takes the decision seriously, listen to Jose Mourinho talk about. Or even Nigeria's head coach (who was beat my Morocco). In the end, Morocco are the champions. Get over it.",2026-03-29T23:30:15Z,2026-03-29T23:31:01Z,0,True,,2026-05-04T02:02:50.015800
AFCON,MU-oq7Nthp8,Ugy9nZDnBD4qSo4pb4F4AaABAg.AUvMhAHohJCAUxgPaRfXY7,Ugy9nZDnBD4qSo4pb4F4AaABAg,@anthonysmurthwaite6258,"​@DMM6not only was I not biased against Morocco, I actually liked Morocco more than Senegal before this ridiculous match, as for the appeals process, it's very weird that the people making this decision are the same people that let Morocco get away with harassing a Senegalese goalkeeper, almost as if there's some bias that would make them lean to certain decision, but since you're I should have no issue with this since it's their legal right, does that mean you'll be okay if it gets overturned again and Senegal wins, or will you cry about it?


Nobody might be a slight exaggeration, but 99.99999999% of people that aren't Moroccan and have no other reason or tendancy to support Morocco outside of the match agree that Morocco didn't win, because I don't know about you, but I tend to think if a team wins a trophy, they actually have to beat the team they're facing, which is what Senegal did, walk off or not, but winning a trophy after getting beat by the team that won the trophy without playing again does nothing, it's not impressive, there's nothing prestigious about winning a trophy in a courtroom, the lawyers are the only people who did anything for Morocco, non of the players or the manager did anything",2026-03-29T23:42:40Z,2026-03-29T23:42:40Z,0,True,,2026-05-04T02:02:50.015805
AFCON,MU-oq7Nthp8,Ugy9nZDnBD4qSo4pb4F4AaABAg.AUvMhAHohJCAUxlRFR-yQf,Ugy9nZDnBD4qSo4pb4F4AaABAg,@DMM6,"@anthonysmurthwaite6258 Here's the thing, your opinion, and those who think like you, is 1000% irrelevant and inconsequential. It changes nothing. You are thinking emotionally and not practically.

The bottom line is this. Senegal abandoned the game. They forfeited the game. Morocco are champions. You cry about it all you want, it changes nothing.

And for what its worth, there are no winners in this situation. Senegal are rightly stripped of the title, and Morocco are robbed of the chance to celebrate with their fans in their own country. Everybody got shafted.",2026-03-30T00:26:35Z,2026-03-30T00:26:35Z,0,True,,2026-05-04T02:02:50.015810
AFCON,MU-oq7Nthp8,Ugy9nZDnBD4qSo4pb4F4AaABAg.AUvMhAHohJCAUxoupIo5WK,Ugy9nZDnBD4qSo4pb4F4AaABAg,@anthonysmurthwaite6258,"​@DMM6 I'm not thinking Emotionally or practically, because I know my opinion is irrelevant just like yours, but the opinion of the vast majority all collectively agreeing that this decision is ridiculous as a collective does make a difference, because this decision has tarnished the trophy

Also saying Morocco were robbed actually made me laugh, so thanks for the chuckle",2026-03-30T00:56:59Z,2026-03-30T00:56:59Z,0,True,,2026-05-04T02:02:50.015815
