Maroc,aRgYcWd6tXw,UgwYf5t1xsQI-5NH0Ch4AaABAg,,@missym877,"Some of yall need to develop a stronger backbone. Whether you’re visiting Morocco, Paris or NYC — if you’re a tourist visiting a touristy area— you’re going to encounter someone looking to sell you something. Learn how to say no and not feel any shame about it and you won’t have a miserable time. I say no to street vendors all the time. I don’t stop, I don’t hold a conversation, I say “no thank you,” and continue firmly walking. A person looking to make money isn’t going to waste their time hassling someone who’s ignoring them and walking on— they’re gonna focus on the person still standing in front of them, talking to them, and acting hesitant in saying no.",2026-04-25T21:17:05Z,2026-04-25T21:17:05Z,0,False,0.0,2026-05-04T02:03:07.096674
