Maroc,aRgYcWd6tXw,UgzoBOglG3qvtu1E04N4AaABAg,,@rachadlaviateur-ss4tq,"I am from Marrakech originally and currently residing in the US. Your comment about Morocco is absolutely true. Even I, was treated the same way you were treated. Unfortunately poverty pushes people to do anything just to survive. As my non Moroccan wife stated once after living there for her first moth: ""to stiff one another has become part of Moroccan tradition"" I was thin about her statement for a while and realize that it is true because I have overheard many times how someone Braggs about his wrongdoing to his camarads as it was such a big accomplishment. So my dear lady I am with 100% and sorry for the experience and let us not forget that not all Morocco follows the same pattern, neither do all Moroccans. There is good and bad in every country. I do hope that those little negativities won't stop you for going back to explore more of our exotic and mystic country because there is a lot more to see in the remote areas and avoid the big cities where a tourist may fall in the trap of the shopkeepers, storytellers and falls tour guides. As for the taxidrivers, the government is now putting their uncalled for behavior under control. Once a cabby is reported concequences are severe",2026-03-24T11:54:39Z,2026-03-24T11:54:39Z,0,False,0.0,2026-05-04T02:03:07.096926
