Tourisme,9qdTCYPrAN0,Ugxevz4XoMPF-9wLuwB4AaABAg,,@donnalockhart,"At last count there were around 500,000 Canadians who own real estate in the USA, Florida mostly but also Arizona too. So many of them want to sell and not go south but elsewhere for the winter months. So don’t expect tourism numbers to drastically drop until the real estate market improves and Canadians can sell. Selling remotely is not an option for many and neither is renting property when Canadian owned. Supply is at 13 month high in Florida and demand has bottomed out. There is much uncertainty in the USA and unless/ until that changes…many Snowbirds are also aging out of this winter exodus and that will help. Other younger generations will be deterred and also indicate they prefer a variety of locations not just one place winter after winter. As long as it takes the results will be the same - this annual migration of Canadian Snowbirds and world wide tourists to the USA will ultimately have a profound impact on tourism dollars. So Florida in particular better get ready to raise taxes on residents cause currently they homestead and pay no State tax if Florida is their 6 month residence. Tourists pay tax that covers many services…double whammy.",2026-05-03T19:10:54Z,2026-05-03T19:10:54Z,0,False,0.0,2026-05-04T02:03:23.571118
